        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Held indoors with thousands in attendance, Detroit Autorama had the potential to become a fabled “super spreader” event. Instead of risking that kind of infamy and the negative impact on the community, Championship Auto Shows and its partner Michigan Hot Rod Association decided to pull the plug.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Last year, the Detroit Autorama snuck through before statewide restrictions were forced on residents and businesses in Michigan.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/04/Detroit-Autorama-Has-Been-Canceled--2.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "image credit: YouTube"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This would have been the 69th annual Autorama, an event many in Detroit, the surrounding area, and beyond look forward to attending each year. To say a lot of fans are feeling disappointment would be an understatement. Some are calling for an Autorama “tribute” ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "event to be held outdoors",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
